\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 About radmind
\f1\b0 \
Radmind is a set of tool that can be used to maintain systems and act as a tripwire for security purposes.\
\

\f0\b Change Log
\f1\b0 \
To see what has been changed in the version see http://www.rsug.itd.umich.edu/software/radmind/changelog.html\
\

\f0\b Requirements\

\f1\b0 Radmind requires a Macintosh running Max OS X 10.1.3 or later.\
\

\f0\b Installing Radmind
\f1\b0 \
This package installs software into standard file locations.  If you have moved /Library/StartupItems, /usr/local/bin, /usr/local/sbin, /usr/local/share/man or /private/var we recommend that you install from the source code rather than using this installer.\
\
You will need administrator privileges to install radmind.  Click on the lock icon in the installer to authenticate as a different user.  The default install includes only the client tools along with some example files.  To install the radmind server, click on customize and select the packages you wish to install.  The client tools are required for all installs.\
